data.title: ZachXBT reveals connection between theft and Garden Finance, with over 25% volume linked to stolen funds. Critics slam platform for aiding illegal activity, including North Korean money laundering.
data.description: An examination has found that more than a quarter of Garden Finance's overall volume, estimated at over 25%, has been connected to funds that were stolen. The platform is under scrutiny and receiving backlash for allegedly enabling unlawful activities, such as aiding in North Korean money laundering schemes.

data.title: Datavault AI responds to Wolfpack Research's malicious short report; affirms strength in data tokenization and management. CEO Nathaniel T. Bradley targeted.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, Datavault AI, a prominent player in data tokenization and management listed on NASDAQ under the ticker DVLT, responded to a negative report by Wolfpack Research targeting the company and its CEO, Nathaniel T. Bradley. The report was described as self-serving and malicious by Datavault AI. The company firmly denounces the report and released an official statement in response.

data.title: Home Depot, Foundation pledge $1 million for Hurricane Melissa relief efforts in Caribbean.
data.description: Atlanta-based retailer The Home Depot and its charitable arm, The Home Depot Foundation, have announced a pledge of $1 million in product donations, nonprofit grants, and additional assistance. This initiative aims to offer both immediate relief and extensive support for the recovery of Jamaica and other Caribbean areas that have been severely impacted by recent events.

data.title: Refined Energy Corp. partners with RMK Marketing for 6-month online marketing program. Stay tuned for updates.
data.description: Refined Energy Corp., listed on the CSE as RUU, OTC as RRUUF, and FRA as CWA0, headquartered in Vancouver, British Columbia, disclosed that they are initiating a marketing program. The Company has partnered with RMK Marketing Inc., located at 541 Lana Terrace, Mississauga, Ontario, Canada L5A 3B2, contactable via email at roberto@rmkmarketing.ca. The marketing services are set to commence around November 17, 2025, with an initial duration of six months. However, management and the Company's board of directors retain the discretion to potentially extend or shorten this period based on the effectiveness of the services provided.

data.title: Hurricane Melissa caused Montego Bay Airport to resume operations after 4 p.m. on Oct. 30 for evacuation & aid flights.
data.description: The Mexican company Grupo Aeroportuario del Pacífico, S.A.B. de C.V. (NYSE: PAC; BMV: GAP) has announced that the Montego Bay International Airport in Jamaica reopened for operations on October 30 at 4 p.m. (local time) following the impact of Hurricane Melissa. The airport is currently facilitating evacuation flights and the delivery of humanitarian aid.

data.title: Pfizer sues Novo Nordisk and Metsera to block $6.5 billion deal.
data.description: Pfizer filed a lawsuit against Metsera and Novo Nordisk last week to halt Novo's planned acquisition of the smaller obesity-focused company for $6.5 billion. The legal action aims to prevent the deal from proceeding, as announced in a report by Investor's Business Daily.
